-- Turkish Central Bank’s Turhan Appointed Head of Stock Exchange
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-01-01T13:34:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-01/turkish-central-bank-s-turhan-appointed-head-of-stock-exchange.html
Ibrahim Turhan, a deputy governor of
 Turkey ’s central bank, was appointed head of the  Istanbul Stock
Exchange , according to a decision published in the Official
Gazette today.  Turhan was named deputy governor in 2008, according to his
biography on the central bank web page.  Turhan replaces the outgoing head of the exchange, Huseyin Erkan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
